{
  "texts": [
    "If the path from vertex u to a vertex w is a meta-path instance, then, we add the vertex connecting u and w to both M[u] and B on lines 7-11.",
    "M[u i] stores the valid vertices in instances where the bifurcations occur at u i, and B stores all the valid vertices that bifurcate.",
    "Note that valid vertices are defined as vertices appearing in instances of the set P of meta-paths.",
    "After this step, the vertices in the set B are combined according to the vertex types in s [i] on lines 13-14.",
    "Next, each vertex in the keyset of Map M is connected to the combined vertex belonging to it, and the type of new edges is updated on lines 15-21. we can efficiently utilize complex semantic information, i.e., meta-structure, to do community search on heterogeneous graphs.Theorem 1 To get the maximum community, the BatchEcore algorithm can be used on the reconstructed graph with the transformed meta-paths."
  ]
}